And do not believe except those who follow your religion; say, "The guidance is the guidance of Allah," and they say: "If you do not believe, they will be guided for what you have been given." Say: "To Allah belongs the grace of Allah and He is the All-Knowing, the All-Knowing."
He gives mercy to whom He pleases, and Allah is the Owner of Great Bounty.
Among the People of the Book are some of the People of the Book, if he is rich in wealth, he will leave you with one of them; and if you find him with a thousand of them, it will not cause you to lose it, and it is because they say, "There is no blame on us." And Allah knows what they say.
Nay, but whoever fulfills his pledge and fears Allah, surely Allah loves those who are pious.
As for those who sell Allah's covenant and their oaths for a small price, they shall have no portion in the Hereafter, nor will He speak to them on the Day of Resurrection, nor will He purify them, nor will He purify them; and for them is a painful punishment.
Among them are some of them who distort the Book with their tongues, so that you may suppose that it is not for the Book, and it is not of the Book; and they say, "This is from Allah." They say, "This is from Allah, and they are liars."
It is not for any human being that Allah has given him the Book and the Prophethood, and He will say to his people, "Worship Me and my Lord."
And He will not enjoin you to worship the angels and the prophets, but He will bring you to unbelief after you have submitted to Him.
And (remember) when Allah took the covenant of the Children of Israel (saying): "I have given you the Book and Wisdom, and then there comes to you a Messenger confirming what is with you, and you shall believe in him and help him."
But whoever turns away after it is the transgressors.
Do they seek other than Allah's religion? To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth, willingly and unwillingly, and to Him shall they return.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "We have believed in Allah and what was sent down to us, Isma'il (Ishmael), Isma'il (Ishmael), Ishaq (Isaac), Ishaq (Isaac), Ya'qub (Moses), and the Tribes and the Prophets and the Prophets and the Prophets and the Prophets and the Prophets and the Prophets, and the Messengers and the Prophets, and the Messengers, and all of them.
And whoever seeks a religion other than Islam, it will never be accepted from him, and in the Hereafter he will be one of the losers.
How will Allah guide a people who disbelieved after they disbelieved, and bore witness that the Messenger is true and the truth came to them? And Allah does not guide the unjust.
These are the ones on whom the curse of Allah is upon them, and the angels, and all of them all together.
They will abide therein forever. Their punishment will not be lightened, nor will they be reprieved.
Except for those who repent and reform; surely Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
Those who disbelieve after their belief, and then increase in disbelief, their repentance will not be accepted, and they are not the losers.
As for those who disbelieve and die while they are disbelievers, it is not accepted for them from the earth, even though it should be accepted for them, and they shall have no helpers, and they shall have no helpers.
By no means shall ye attain righteousness unless ye spend out of that which ye love; and whatever ye spend, verily, Allah is Knowing of it.
All food were lawful for the Children of Israel, which was given to the Children of Israel that which was sent down before them. Say: "Bring the Torah, if you are truthful."
And whoever fabricates a lie against Allah, it is they who are the wrongdoers.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Allah has spoken the truth, so follow the religion of Ibrahim (Abraham) Hanifa (Islamic Monotheism), and he was not of the polytheists."
Verily, the first House (of worship) established for mankind was that at Makkah, blessed and a guidance.
There are signs in the signs of Abraham; and whoever enters it, it is safe to him; and whoever enters the House, it is safe for him; and whoever disbelieves, then surely Allah is Independent of the worlds.
Say, "O People of the Book, why do you reject the signs of Allah?"
Say, "O followers of the Book, why do you prevent those who believe from Allah's way, seeking to prevent them from the path of Allah? But you are not aware of what you do."
O you who believe! If you obey a party of those who were given the Book, they would turn you back after you have believed.
And how will you disbelieve? How can you disbelieve in Allah's revelations and His Messenger? And whoever is in charge of Allah, He will guide you to a straight path.
O you who have believed, fear Allah as He should be feared and do not die except as Muslims.
And hold fast to the rope of Allah, and do not be divided in yourselves; and remember Allah's favour upon you when you were enemies, and He made your hearts into your hearts; and you were brothers of the Fire, and you were saved by the fire, and He saved you from the fire, so that you may be guided.
And among you there shall be a party who invite to righteousness, and enjoin what is right and forbid what is wrong; and it is they who are the successful.
Be not like those who are divided amongst themselves and fall into disputations after receiving Clear Signs; for them is a great punishment.
On the day when some faces will be whitened, and some faces will turn black, and those whose faces are black will be black to those whose faces are black. Then taste the punishment for what you used to disbelieve.
And those whose faces are whitened, they will abide in God's mercy; they will abide therein forever.
These are the Signs of Allah which We rehearse to you in truth; and Allah does not wish to do injustice to any of the worlds.
To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth; and to Him is all things.
You are the best of the righteous, and what is right for you, and forbid what is right, and forbid those who believe and believe in Allah and the Book.
They will not harm you except harm; if they fight against you, they will turn their backs against you, and they will not be helped.
There is no refuge in the people except by Allah, except for the people, and the people, and they will have to draw near to Allah's wrath; and for them is a curse from Allah, and that they may not disobey the prophets, and they will slay the prophets, and they will slay the prophets, and they are transgressors.
They are not all alike; there is a party of the People of the Book who recite the Signs of Allah during periods of the night and recite the prayer.
They believe in Allah and the Last Day; they enjoin what is right and forbid what is wrong; and they hasten in the way of righteousness; and they are the best of the righteous.
And whatever good they do, they will not be denied it; and Allah knows well those who are pious.
As for those who disbelieve, neither their properties nor their children will avail them against Allah; they are the dwellers of the Fire, and they will abide therein.
That which they spend in the life of this world is a likeness of the like of that which is kindled in the midst of the people who have wronged themselves, and it destroys it, and it is not for them to destroy it; but it is they who are wronged.
O you who believe! Do not take your friends other than your own selves; they will not be able to harm you in the way of you; they love the hatred of their mouths, and hide their breasts; surely it is greater to make clear to you the signs; surely We have made clear to you the communications.
You are those who love them, and they love you not, and you believe in the Book, and when they meet you they say: We believe in their rage. Say: Die in your rage; surely Allah knows what is in the breasts; surely Allah knows what is in the breasts.
If good befalls you, it grieves them; but if a misfortune befalls you, they rejoice at it, and if you are patient, their guile will not harm you. God encompasses what they do.
And (remember) when you (O Muhammad sal-Allaahu 'alayhe wa sallam) entered your family in the morning to battle at the stations of battle; and Allah is Hearing, Knowing.
(Remember) when two parties against you (O Muhammad sal-Allaahu 'alayhe wa sallam) was against you, but Allah was their protector; and the believers put their trust in Allah.
And Allah had helped you at Badr when you were weak, so fear Allah, so that you may be grateful.
Remember when you said to the believers, "Is it not enough for you that your Lord should reinforce you with three thousand angels sent down?"
Nay, but if you are patient, and fear Allah, and they will attack you suddenly, your Lord will reinforce you with five thousand angels.
And Allah did not send it except for good news and that your hearts may be calm to your hearts; and Allah is Mighty, Wise.
That He may cut off a section of those who disbelieve, or abase them, so that they may turn away from evil.
There is no concern in your decision; He pardons them or punishes them; surely they are unjust.
To Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on earth; He forgives whom He wills and punishes whom He pleases; and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
O you who have believed, do not consume usury, doubled and multiplied, and fear Allah that you may prosper.
And fear the Fire for those who disbelieve.
And obey Allah and the Messenger that you may receive mercy.
And hasten to forgiveness from your Lord and a garden as wide as the heavens and the earth, prepared for the righteous.
Those who spend (benevolently) in prosperity and hardship, and who restrain anger and pardon men; and Allah loves the doers of good.
And those who, when they have committed an indecency, or wronged themselves, remember Allah and implore forgiveness for their sins, and who forgiveth sins except Allah?
Their reward is forgiveness from their Lord, and Gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever; and how excellent is the reward of those who work!
Many have passed away before you, so travel through the earth and see what was the end of those who disbelieved.
This is a declaration for mankind, and a guidance and a reminder for the pious.
And do not grieve, nor grieve, and you will be superior, if you are believers.
If a wound has touched you, it is the same of those who disbelieve, and We shall make them revert to the people of the people; and that Allah may know the believers and some of you from among you; and Allah does not love the unjust.
And that Allah may test those who believe and reject the disbelievers.
Do you think that Allah knows not those who strive hard among you, and He knows those who are patient?
And indeed you wish for death before you have seen it, and you have seen it.
Muhammad (peace be upon him) is the Messenger of Allah. And if he dies, he is not of the Messengers; then if he dies, he will turn back on your heels; and whoever turns back on his heels, then surely Allah will not harm them, and Allah will reward the thankful.
And there is no death except by Allah's permission, except for a single soul; and whoever desires the reward of this world, We shall give him of it; and whoever desires the reward of the Hereafter, We shall give him thereof, and We shall reward him for a reward.
And how many a prophet has fought in Allah's house; so they did not become weak for them in the way of Allah, nor did they weaken in the way of Allah, nor did they weaken; and Allah loves the patient.
They did not say, "Our Lord, forgive us our sins and our transgressions, and make our foothold firm, and protect us from the disbelieving people."
So Allah gave them the reward of this world and the Hereafter, and Allah loves the righteous.
O you who believe! If you obey those who disbelieve, they will turn you back on your heels, and you will be losers.
Nay, Allah is your Protector, and He is the Best of helpers.
“Soon shall We cast terror into the hearts of the Unbelievers, for that they joined partners with Allah for which He had sent down no authority; and their abode is the Fire; and evil is the destination.”
And Allah has promised the promise of your promise, so that you should slay them, so that you should kill him, and argue in that wherein you have been given, and that you may differ in the matter of Allah, and that you may turn away from what you have been given, and He has made you successors from among you. He has made you successors from among you, and He has made you successors. And Allah is the Owner of the believers.
And when you turned away, there was no one for him, and the Messenger was calling you back from your rear, so He seized you from grief for grief, so that you might not grieve for what escaped escaped upon you, nor grieve for what befell you; and Allah is aware of what you do.
Then He made a veil for you (O Muhammad SAW) as a group of a group of a group of a group of a group of a group, and some of a group of a group of a group, and some of them were averse to their disbelief. They said, "What is it that you have been doing?" They said, "What is this for us?" Say, "We have been given what is in your homes. God knows what is in your hearts. God knows what is in your hearts. God knows what is in your hearts. God knows what is in your hearts. God knows what is in your hearts."
Those of you who turned back on the day when the two hosts met, Satan made them slip for some of them; and Allah has pardoned them; surely Allah is Forgiving, Forbearing.
O you who believe! Be not like those who disbelieve, when their brethren should be travelling in the earth when they walk in the earth or they say, "If they had been with us, they would not have died, nor would they have been killed; so that Allah may make a regret in their hearts and die, and Allah sees all that you do."
And if you are slain in the way of Allah, then forgiveness from Allah and mercy from Allah are better than what they amass.
And if you die or die, then to Allah you shall be gathered.
So it was due to mercy from Allah that you deal with them gently; and had you been rough, hard hearted, they would have dispersed from around you. So pardon them and ask forgiveness for them and consult them in the affair; then when you have decided, then place your trust in Allah; surely Allah loves those who trust.
If Allah helps you, there is none who can overcome you; and if He forsakes you, then who can help you after Him?
And there is not for any prophet any prophet, nor will he disobey him with what he has earned; then every soul will be paid in full for what it has earned, and they will not be wronged.
Is he who followeth Allah's pleasure like he who draws away from Allah's wrath, whose abode is Hell, and evil is the destination?
They are grades of God, and God sees what they do.
God did confer a great favour on the believers when He sent among them a Messenger from among themselves, reciting to them His verses and purifying them and teaching them the Book and Wisdom, while before that they were in manifest error.
And when a calamity befell you when you were afflicted twice twice you were afflicted with a twice twice. Say: "This is from your own selves; surely Allah has power over all things."
And what befell you on the day when the two armies met with Allah's leave was made by the believers, and that He might know the believers.
And He said to the hypocrites, "Come to fight in Allah's cause, or fight in the way of Allah." They said, "If we had been forbidden to war, we would certainly have been given you." They will say, "We have been nearer to you." They say, "In the way of Allah, what is in their hearts, and Allah knows what they hide."
They are those who say to their brothers, "If they had been given us, they would not have been killed." Say: "Avert death from death, if you are truthful."
And do not think of those who are killed in Allah's way as dead; nay, they are alive, provided their sustenance with their Lord.
They rejoice in what Allah has bestowed upon them by His bounty, and those who are behind them, for those who are behind them, and those who are behind them, they shall have no fear, nor shall they grieve.
They rejoice in the grace of Allah and His blessings; and Allah does not waste the reward of the believers.
Those who responded to the Messenger of Allah and the Messenger after Allah had given them a great reward, and for those of them who do good, theirs is a great reward.
Those to whom the people said: "Verily, the people have gathered against you, so fear them," but they increased their faith, and they said: "Allah is sufficient for us, and He is the Best of Guardians."
So they returned from Allah's grace and grace; no harm touched them; and they followed the pleasure of Allah, and Allah is the Owner of Great Bounty.
It is Satan who frightens you, so fear them not, but fear Me, if you are believers.
And let not those who disbelieve fall into disbelief for those who disbelieve; they will not harm Allah at least they will not harm them in the Hereafter; and for them is a great punishment.
Those who purchase disbelief for their disbelief will not harm Allah, and theirs is a painful punishment.
And let not those who disbelieve think that Our granting them respite is better for them; We grant them respite only for their sins; and for them is a humiliating punishment.
It is not for Allah that you should cause the believers to turn away from it; and Allah does not know the evil of the evil-doers; but Allah knows what He pleases of the unseen, and He chooses His messengers whom He pleases; so believe in Allah and His Messengers.
And let not those who do not think that what Allah has given them of His grace is better for them; it is better for them that they are niggardly; nay, it is worse for them to be niggardly on their necks on the Day of Resurrection and their necks on the Day of Resurrection; and Allah is aware of what you do.
Allah has heard the saying of those who say: Allah is the Most Gracious, and we are rich for the rich and we are rich for what they have said, and We shall say to the prophets, "Taste the punishment of the Fire and taste the punishment."
This is because of what your hands have sent before, and that Allah is not unjust to His servants.
They say: "Allah has promised us that we should not believe in any messenger unless he brings us a sacrifice." Say, "Messengers before you have come to you with clear proofs and with which you have come to the fire." Then you did slay them, if you are truthful.
But if they reject you, they were Messengers before you, who came before them with clear proofs and scriptures, and the Book of Enlightenment.
Every soul will have a taste of death; and you will not be paid your only reward on the Day of Resurrection; then whoever is admitted to the Fire, he is admitted to the Garden, and the life of this world is but the enjoyment of the world.
You shall surely be tested in your wealth and in your souls, and you will surely hear from those who were given the Book before you and from those who were given the Book. But if you are patient, and fear Allah, then surely it is the matter of the matter.
And (remember) when Allah took a covenant from the People of the Book (i.e. the Qur'an) to make it clear to mankind, and it was not plain to mankind that they threw their backs (their backs), so they threw their backs in their backs, so that they would turn away from their backs, and it is evil for them.
Do not think that those who rejoice in what they have been given, and that they should be praised for what they have not been given, and do not think of them the punishment of the punishment; for them is a painful punishment.
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth; and Allah has power over all things.
The creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of night and day, are signs for those who understand.
Those who remember Allah, standing, sitting, and lying on their sides, and reflect on the creation of the heavens and the earth, (saying): "Our Lord, You have not created this in vain.
Our Lord! You whom You admit to the Fire, You have disgraced him, and there is no helpers for the unjust.
O our Lord! We have heard the call of a caller calling to faith: "Believe in your Lord," and we have believed, so forgive us our Lord, and forgive us from evil.
Our Lord! You have promised us what Thou hast promised us through Thy Messengers and disgrace us not on the Day of Resurrection; surely Thou wilt not break the promise.
So their Lord answered them: "I shall not be among you any human being, nor of you, nor of you, nor of you, nor of you, and to take place for you from your homes; and I will place for you from your homes, and I will admit you to Gardens beneath which rivers flow, and that which is in the garden, will be the reward of Allah; and Allah is the best of the best."
Let not the earth deceive you in the land.
That is a brief enjoyment, and their abode is Hell, and evil is the destination.
But as for those who fear their Lord, they will have gardens beneath which rivers flow; therein they shall abide therein for ever; and that which is with Allah is the best of the righteous.
And there are some of the People of the Book who believe in Allah and that which has been sent down to you, and that they have been sent down to those who have been sent down to Allah; they have no small price in the communications of Allah; they have their reward with their Lord; surely Allah is swift in reckoning.
O you who believe! Endure in patience and remain steadfast and remain steadfast, and fear Allah that you may prosper.
O mankind! fear your Lord, who created you from a single soul, and from him created his mate, and from his mate, and from many men and women; and fear Allah in Whom you demand one of your rights, and the wombs of the wombs; surely Allah is Witness over you.
And give the orphans their wealth, and do not exchange it for good, and do not devour their property for their property; surely this is a great sin.
And if ye fear that ye shall not marry the orphan, if ye marry one of your wives, or two, or four, or four; or if ye fear that ye shall not be able to do justice; but if ye fear not, it is better for you; that is that which ye do not.
And give the women their dowries as a gift; but if they remit any of you, they will consume it with wholesome appetite.
And do not give your wealth to the poor, that Allah has made for you a provision which He has made for you, and brings them out of it, and clothe them with gentle words.
And marry the orphans until they are given them; then if you find them in the right hand, then give them their property; and do not eat of them, and do not fear them; and for the poor, it is for them; and whoever is good for them, then let him take care of their property; and Allah is sufficient in need.
That is what the property of the parents and the property of his parents, and the wives of their parents, and the wives of their parents, or the women, or the women, or a small number.
And when the orphans and the orphans and the needy are needy, give them out of it, and speak to them honourable words.
And fear those who fear them, if they were weak offspring, they would fear them; so let them fear Allah, and speak words of righteousness.
As for those who consume the wealth of the orphans, they will consume their bellies in their bellies, and they will roast in Hell.
Allah has prescribed to you your sons, that he may marry two wives for their wives, and the wives of their wives; and if they marry, it is better for them; and it is not for them that he may bring forth his wife, except for his wife; and if it is written for them, then there is no blame for them except for the sake of Allah; and if it is decreed for them, then there is no blame for them from Allah; surely Allah is Knowing, Wise.
And your wives have been given to you that He has taken for them a son, and if a son had taken a son, he would have given him a son, and if he had taken a child, he would have given them wives, and if you have not taken a child, then there is no one who has taken away from them; and if you have a child, then there is no blame for them except for what you have been given, or for what you have been given; and if you have a child, then there is no blame for them.
These are the limits of Allah; and whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, He will admit him into Gardens under which rivers flow, abiding therein forever; and that is the great attainment.
And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger, and transgresses His limits, He will admit him into the Fire, to abide therein; and he shall have a disgraceful punishment.
And those of your wives who are guilty of lewdness, bring four witnesses against you from among them; and if they testify, confine them to the houses until death overtakes them, or Allah ordain for them a way.
And for those of you who are guilty of indecency, kill them both; but if they repent and amend, turn away from them; surely Allah is Oft-Returning, Most Merciful.
Allah accepts the repentance of those who do evil in ignorance, and then repent of their sins; and Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise.
And of no effect is the repentance of those who continue to do evil, until death faces one of them, and he says, "Now I repent," nor of those who die while they die. We have prepared for them a painful punishment.
O you who believe! It is not lawful for you to inherit the marriage of your wives; nor do you make them clear to them that you may have given them a part of that which you have given them, and do not turn away from them, so that you may not be able to harm them; surely Allah is good for what you do.
And if you wish to take one another for another, and do not have given a portion of them in the least, then do not turn away from it, and do not turn away from it, and do not commit evil.
And how can you take out of what you have earned, and have taken a covenant from you?
And marry not women whom your fathers married, except for what has passed before; surely it is shameful and hateful, and an evil way.
It is your father who has given you your wife, and your wives, and your wives, and the women, and your family, and your family, and your family, and your family, and your family, and your mothers, and your spouses, and your spouses, and your spouses, and your spouses, and your wives; surely Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
And your wives are only those whom your right hands possess, except for Allah's permission; and it is written for you, except for them, except for your property, and do not commit adultery except for your wives; for you have given your wives as a marriage for them; for Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise.
And those who do not marry among you who are in the hearts of the believing men, the men of the hearts of men, will be among those who have believed, and Allah knows well those who are faithful, and He knows best those who are faithful to you; and if you do not give them a share, they will not be able to marry them except for what is due to them, and you shall not be able to kill them; and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
God desires to make clear to you and to show you the ordinances of those before you; and He will turn to you in mercy, and God is All-Knowing, All-Wise.
Allah desires to turn to you, and those who follow their lusts wish that you should deviate far away.
Allah wants to lighten your burden, and man was created weak.
O you who believe! Do not devour yourselves in the property of yourselves, except by mutual consent of your own selves; and do not kill yourselves; surely Allah is Merciful, Merciful.
And whoever commits aggression and transgression, We shall cast him into Hell, and that is easy for Allah.
If you avoid the major sins which you have been forbidden, We will remove your sins from you, and admit you to a noble place.
Do not covet what Allah has given you above others; for men is a share of what they earn, and for women is a portion of what they earn; and Allah has full knowledge of all things; surely Allah is Knowing of everything.
And We have made heirs of all of his parents and kinsmen, and those who have made a covenant with those whom you have made with your covenant; surely Allah is Witness over everything.
Men are the children of Allah; He has made some of them excel others from among others; and they spend their wealth in their wealth, and that they may spend the good women, and the women who are careful of the piety of Allah, and those who do not know them, do not take them out of their hands; and if they obey you, they will not have touched them; surely Allah is Mighty, Merciful.
And if you fear a breach between them twain, appoint him from his family from his family and from his family, if they wish for peace, Allah will cause their reconciliation; surely Allah is Knowing, Aware.
And worship Allah, and do not associate with Him any partners, nor do your parents, and the orphans, the orphans, the orphans, the orphans, the needy, the companion, the companion, your companion, and your companion, and your companion, and the wayfarer; surely Allah loves not the arrogant.
Those who are niggardly, and enjoin the people, and enjoin out of what Allah has given them of His bounty, and We have prepared for the disbelievers a humiliating punishment.
And those who spend their wealth to be seen of men, and they do not believe in Allah and the Last Day; and whoever is Satan, he is an evil companion.
And what was it that they had believed in Allah and the Last Day, and spend out of what He has given them, and Allah knows what they have earned?
Allah does not wrong the atom's weight of injustice; but if any good is good, He doubles it, and gives him a great reward.
How will it be when We bring forth from every nation a witness, and We bring you as a witness against them?
On that day those who disbelieved and disobeyed the Messenger will wish that they were buried on the earth, and they will not be able to hide it from Allah.
O you who believe! Do not approach prayer until you speak to yourselves, unless you know what you say, and you will not go forth except your backs, and you shall find it, or you are sick, or if you are sick, there is no one of you or you, and you are the one who is the <unk>, and your hands, and your hands; and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
Have you not seen those who were given a portion of the Book, purchasing error, and wish to turn away from you from the Right Path?
And Allah knows your enemies, and Allah is sufficient as a protector; and Allah is sufficient as a protector.
Those who have been given to the Jews, they have been given to them, and they will not be able to talk about them, and they will say, "This is better." They will say, "We have listened to you," and they will be able to say, "This is better for them." But Allah has cursed them for their unbelief, so that they may not believe.
O People of the Book! Believe in what We have sent down to you, before We turn away from them, before We turn away from them, and We turn them away from their backs, and We cursed them as We cursed the Sabbath.
Surely Allah does not forgive that partners should be set up with Him, but He forgives anything else for whom He wills.
Have you not seen those whom they say, "Nay, but Allah wills whom He wills." They will not be wronged, nor will they be wronged.
See how they forge a lie against Allah, and that is a manifest sin.
Have you not seen those who were given a portion of the Book that they had been given the Book and Satan, and those who disbelieve say, "These are better than the believers who are guided?"
They are those whom Allah has cursed, and whom Allah curses, you will not find for him any helper.
Is there any one of them in the kingdom, so that they may not be able to give the people a little more?
Or do they envy the people because of what Allah has given them of His bounty, so We gave to the Children of Abraham the Book and the Wisdom, and We gave them a great kingdom?
There are some of them who believe in the Book, and some of them turn away from it; and sufficient is Hell.
As for those who disbelieve in Our revelations, We shall cast them into Hell; as often as their skins are roasted, We shall change them for some skins, so that they may taste the punishment; surely Allah is Mighty, Wise.
As for those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, We shall admit them to Gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. These are spouses, and We shall admit them to deepening shade.
