O you who believe! do not take the Jews and the Christians for friends; they are friends of each other; and whoever amongst you takes them for a friend, then surely he is one of them; surely Allah does not guide the unjust people.
And you see those in whose hearts is a disease hastening towards them. They say: "We fear lest some misfortune befall us." Then Allah will bring a victory from Allah, or He will bring down a veil from their hearts, and they will be remorseful in their hearts.
And those who believe will say: "Are these the people who swore by Allah that they were with you?" Their deeds have become vain, and they are losers.
O you who believe! If any of you turn back from his religion, then Allah will bring forth a people whom He will love, and they will love Him, who will love Him, lowly in the cause of the believers and the censure of the critic; surely Allah is the Owner of bounties and His mercy.
Your guardian is only Allah and His Messenger and those who believe, those who establish prayer and pay the zakat, and they bow down.
And whoever takes Allah and His Messenger and those who believe, then surely the party of Allah is the victorious.
O you who believe! Do not take for those who were given the Book those who were given the Book before you and those who were given you, and do not take the unbelievers as friends for you, so fear Allah, if you are believers.
And when you call to prayer, they take it as a mockery and sport; this is because they are a people who understand.
Say: "O People of the Book! do you disapprove of us that we believe in Allah and what has been sent down to us and that which was sent down to us and that which was sent down before?
Say: "Shall I inform you of something worse than that of Allah? those whom Allah has cursed by His wrath, His wrath, His wrath, and those whom He has made apes, and those whom He has made apes, and those who are far astray, are worse than those who are far astray."
And when they come to you, they say: "We believe"; but they are with those who disbelieve with their unbelief, and Allah knows best what they hide.
And you see many of them in sin and transgression, and in the unlawful, and the unlawful, and what they do is evil.
Why do they not forbid the rabbis and the rabbis, and forbid their devouring of their property? Evil is what they do.
And the Jews say: "Allah's Hand is on hand"; their hands are niggardly, and their hands are cursed by their hands; but it is not except for them that they are niggardly in the hands of their hands; and that which is revealed to them, it is for Allah's sake; and it is not for those who disbelieve in Allah and the earth, and Allah does not love the mischief.
And if the People of the Book had believed and feared Allah, We would have absolved them from their sins and admitted them into Gardens of bliss.
And if they had believed in the Torah and the Gospel and that which was sent down to them from their Lord, they would have taken out from above them and from beneath beneath beneath beneath them; and some of them are a party of them; and many of them are evil.
O Messenger, deliver what has been sent down to you from your Lord; and if you do not, you have not delivered His message; and Allah will protect you from the people; surely Allah does not guide the unbelieving people.
Say: "O People of the Book! ye shall not stand unless ye uphold the Torah and the Gospel and the Gospel which has been sent down to you from your Lord; and that which has been sent down to you from your Lord, He will surely increase many of them in their inordinacy; surely the unbelievers do not grieve."
Those who believe, and those who are Jews, and the Christians, and the Christians, whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day and does righteous good deeds shall have no fear, nor shall they grieve.
We took a covenant from the Children of Israel, and We sent Messengers to them, whenever a Messenger came to them with what they desired, and some of them were impostors.
And they thought that there is no sin, so they became blind, and they became blind; then Allah has turned away from them, and many of them became blind; and Allah sees what they do.
Surely they say: Surely Allah is the Messiah, the son of Mary, and the Messiah said: O Children of Israel, worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord.
They are those who say: Surely Allah is the third of those who are partners; there is no god but He; there is no god except Him; if they do not desist from what they say, there is a painful punishment for those who disbelieve.
Do they not turn to Allah and seek His forgiveness? Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
The Messiah, son of Mary, was no more than a messenger; many of them passed away before him; and his mother was a truthful woman; and his mother said to them: Look at the signs.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Do you worship besides Allah that which has no power to harm you or benefit you? And Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
Say, "O People of the Book, do not exceed the limits in your religion, nor follow the desires of those who have gone astray before, and have misled many of them, and have strayed from the Right Path."
Those who disbelieved from among the Children of Israel were cursed by the tongue of David and Jesus, Jesus son of Mary, because they disobeyed and persisted in excesses.
They did not forbid one another, for what they did.
You see many of them befriending those who disbelieve. Evil is that which their souls have sent before them, so that Allah will be displeased with them and they will abide therein forever.
And had they believed in Allah and the Prophet and that which was sent down to him, they would not have taken them as friends; but many of them are transgressors.
You will surely see the people of the Jews and the idolaters, and those who are faithful to those who are faithful, and those who say, "We are those who are Christians, and those who say, 'We are those who are the ones who are the ones who are among them, and they are not arrogant.'
And when they hear what has been revealed to the Messenger, you will see their eyes overflowing with tears because they recognize the truth; they say: "Our Lord! we believe, so write us down among the witnesses."
And why should we not believe in Allah and the Truth which has come to us, seeing that our Lord will admit us among the righteous people?
And Allah has rewarded them with Gardens beneath which rivers flow, wherein they will abide therein forever. Such is the reward of the righteous.
But those who reject Faith and belie Our Signs, they are the companions of the Fire.
O you who believe! Do not forbid the good things which Allah has made lawful for you, and do not transgress limits; surely Allah does not love the transgressors.
And eat of what Allah has provided for you, lawful and good, and fear Allah in Whom you believe.
Allah has sworn to you by a covenant in your oaths, and that you may not have any oaths in your oaths, and that you may take it away from that which is in your hands, so that they may not be able to eat of the women, except that the women may feed it, or let them take hold of it; and do not bear witness to Allah for His command.
O you who believe! intoxicants and gambling and divining arrows and divining arrows are Satan's handiwork; so avoid them, so that you may prosper.
Satan desires to stir enmity between you and gambling, lest you turn away from Allah and the remembrance of the Remembrance and from the remembrance of Allah. Will you then abstain?
And obey Allah and obey the Messenger; and if you turn away, then know that your duty is only to convey the duty of the Noble Messenger.
There is no blame on those who believe and do righteous deeds, that they may have no sin in the past, but they fear, and do righteous deeds, and do righteous deeds, and do righteous deeds, and do righteous deeds; and Allah loves the righteous.
O you who believe! Allah has given you some of your own hands and your lances, so that Allah may test him who fears Him in secret. And whoever transgresses after him, he is a painful punishment.
O you who believe! Do not enter in the land, nor do you know of it; and for those who know him, then He is the one who has killed you, except for a group of you who fight against one another, except for a party who is fighting against you, or let him die in the sight of Allah; and Allah is Mighty, Mighty.
It is lawful for you to eat of the sea, and to eat it for you, and for the needy and for the wayfarer; and you are forbidden to the land for which you are forbidden; and fear Allah is to Whom you shall be gathered.
Allah has made the Ka'bah the Ka'bah for the Sacred House, and the Sacred House, and the Sacred Month, and the Sacred Month, and the Sacred House, and that you may know that Allah knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth; and Allah knows all things.
Know that Allah is severe in punishment and that Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
The duty of the Messenger is only to convey the message; and Allah knows what you hide and what you hide.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "The hypocrites are not the best of the good and the good, but the abundance of the abundance of Allah, so fear Allah, so that you may prosper."
O you who believe! Do not question about what is clear to you if it is clear to you, and if you ask about what is revealed to you, they will be disclosed to you. Allah has forgiven you, and Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
A people before you asked him, and then they disbelieved in it.
Allah has not forbidden a camel, nor a camel, nor a camel, or a Hami, and a lie, and a lie for those who reject Allah.
And when it is said to them, "Come to what Allah has sent down and to the Messenger," they say, "Sufficient for us is what we found our fathers doing."
O you who believe! Guard your own souls. If you are guided, there will not harm you any harm. To Allah is your return. He will inform you of what you did.
O you who believe! If one of you is dead, then We bring you two hundred of the two of you; but if you wish to travel in the land, then you are one of them; and if you doubt, then the death of you is death, and if you doubt, they will not be able to give any benefit for them; and if they are in doubt, they will not be able to swear by Allah; surely Allah bears witness that they are sinners.
But if it had been discovered that they are guilty of those who are guilty of the wrong of their wives, they are two among those who have taken their homes from among themselves, and they swear by Allah: "Our testimony is truer than our testimony, and we have not transgressed, and we are not of the unjust."
That it may be better that they should be able to bear witness to their oaths, or their oaths will be after their oaths; and fear Allah, and listen to Allah, and Allah does not guide the transgressing people.
On the Day when Allah will gather together all the Messengers, He will say: "What did you answer?" They will say: "We have no knowledge. You are the Knower of the unseen."
And when Jesus, son of Mary, said: "The son of Mary, I will give you his mother, and his mother, and your mother, and I will give you the strength of a people in this world and in the earth, and I will recite it to you in the Book, and I will recite it to you in the Book, and I will bring you out of the Book of Allah, when the people of the Children of Israel say, "This is nothing but obvious magic." And when you have come to Me, those who disbelieved with you have come to you with clear proofs, and those who disbelieve will come to you.
And when I said to the disciples, "Believe in Me and My Messenger," they said: "We believe and bear witness that we are Muslims."
When the disciples said, "O Jesus, son of Mary, is your Lord able to send down to us a table from heaven?" He said, "Fear God, if you are believers."
They said: "We wish that we may eat of it, and satisfy our hearts, and know that we have spoken to you the truth, and that we may be of the witnesses."
Said Jesus, the son of Mary, "O Allah, our Lord, send down to us a table [spread with food] from heaven, that it may be for us to be a festival for the first of us and the last of us and a sign from You.
Allah said: "I will send it down to you, but if you turn away from him, I will surely punish him with a severe punishment in the world."
And when Allah said, "O Jesus, son of Mary, did you say to mankind: 'You have no other gods besides me, and my mother, and my mother?' They will say, "Glory be to you! I know that I am truthful. I know what is in my hearts, and I do not know what is in your hearts. You are the All-Knowing, the All-Knowing."
Never said to them aught except what Thou didst command me to say: worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord; and I was a witness over them whilst I dwelt amongst them; when Thou didst take me up Thou wast the Watcher over them, and Thou art a witness over all things.
If You punish them, they are Your servants, and if You forgive them, You are the Mighty, the Wise.
Allah will say: This is the day on which the truthful will profit their truthfulness; theirs will be Gardens underneath which rivers flow, abiding therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him; this is the great success.
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and He has power over all things.
All praise is due to Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, and made light and light; then those who disbelieve are equal to their Lord.
It is He who created you from clay, then decreed a specified term, and a term of Him is a specified term.
And He is Allah in the heavens and in the earth; He knows what you conceal and what you earn.
No sign comes to them from their Lord, but they turn away from it.
Indeed, they denied the truth when it came to them, but the coming of the Hour will come to them.
Do they not see how many a generation We destroyed before them, whom We had established in the earth, whom We had not given you? We have given them abundant rain from the sky, and We made the rivers flow beneath them, so We destroyed them for their sins, and raised after them a new creation.
And if We had sent down to you a Book on paper, and they touched it with their hands, those who disbelieved would have said, "This is nothing but obvious magic."
And they say, "Why has not an angel been sent down to him?" If We sent down an angel, they would have been given it, and they would not be reprieved.
And if We had made him an angel, We would have made him a man, and We would have made them as confused as they have confused.
Messengers before you were mocked, but those who mocked them were encompassed by what they mocked.
Say: "Travel in the land and see how was the end of those who denied (the Truth)!"
Say: "To whom belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth?" Say: "To Allah belongs the provision for whom He has made mercy. He will surely gather you together on the Day of Resurrection wherein there is no doubt.
To Him belongs whatever is in the night and the day; and He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knowing.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Shall I take for myself other than Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth? He feeds and gives sustenance for His sustenance." Say: "I am commanded to be the first of those who believe, and do not be of the polytheists."
Say, "I fear, if I disobey my Lord, the punishment of a great day."
On the day when it is averted from him, Allah has mercy on him, and that is the manifest achievement.
And if Allah afflicts you with affliction, there is none who can remove it except Him; and if He touches you with good, He has power over all things.
He is Omnipotent, and He is the All-Wise, the All-Aware.
Say: "What is the greatest among them? Say: "Allah has a witness between me and you." Say: "Allah has sent down a witness for you. He has sent down to you the Qur'an. Do you not say, "There is no god but Allah, and you are the partners of Allah."
Those to whom We have given the Book recognize it as they recognize their sons, but those who have lost their souls will not believe.
Who is more unjust than one who invents a lie against Allah or denies His signs? Surely the unjust will not prosper.
On the Day when We gather them all together, then We will say to those who associated partners with Allah: "Where are your partners whom you used to assert?"
Then they will not be asked to say, "By Allah, our Lord, we were not polytheists."
See how they lie against their idols, and that they will turn away from them.
There are some of them who listen to you, and We have made their hearts veils in their hearts, and We have ears to understand their ears; but if they see each of them, they will not believe in it. Those who disbelieve will come to you with clear arguments. Those who disbelieve say, "These are nothing but tales of the ancients."
And they turn away from them, and they turn away from them, and they only destroy themselves, and they do not perceive.
And if you could see when they are made to stand on the Fire, they will say, "Would that we had been sent back, and we would not reject the Signs of our Lord, and we are believers."
Nay, it is that which they used to hide before them; but if they were returned to them, they would surely have been forbidden to it, and they are indeed liars.
And they say: There is nothing but our life in this world, and we shall not be raised up again.
And if you could see when they are made to stand before their Lord, He will say, "Is this not the truth?" They will say, "Yes, by our Lord!" He will say, "Taste the punishment of your disbelief."
Those who reject Allah's meeting with him are losers, until the Hour comes upon them, and they say, "We have neglected what we used to earn." They will be their backs on their necks, and they will be their backs.
And the life of this world is naught but amusement and diversion; and the abode of the Hereafter is better for those who fear Allah, then do you not understand?
We know that they say that which they say grieves you; it is not you that they deny, but the signs of Allah are the liars.
Messengers were denied before you, but they were patient, and they were patient, and they were patient until Our help came to them. There is no changing the words of Allah.
And if their aversion is hard for you, then if you can seek a tunnel into the earth, or a ladder in the sky, or bring them a sign, then bring them a sign; and if Allah had willed, He could have guided them all, so do not be of the ignorant.
Those who listen to Him, they will be called to Him; and Allah will resurrect them on the Day of Resurrection.
And they say, "Why has not a sign been sent down to him from his Lord?" Say, "God has power over them; but most of them do not know."
There is no creature crawling on the earth, nor a bird flying on its wings, but they are like you as you are. We have not neglected anything in the Book, and to their Lord they shall be gathered.
And those who reject Our Signs are deaf and dumb, and in darkness, whom He wills; and whomsoever He wills, He leaves astray whom He pleases.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Tell me, if the punishment of Allah is upon you, or the Hour (i.e. the Day of Resurrection), should you invoke besides Allah, if you are truthful?"
Nay, but He will call upon Him, and He will remove whatever you call upon Him, and you will forget for Him what you associate with Him.
And indeed We sent Messengers before you (O Muhammad SAW), and We seized them with poverty and hardship, so that they might humble themselves.
So when Our punishment came to them, they did not humble themselves, but their hearts were hardened, and Satan made their deeds seem fair.
So when they forgot what they had been reminded of, We opened them to the gates of all of them, and We seized them with what they had been doing; so they were in despair.
So the wrong-doers were cut off, and all praise is due to Allah, the Lord of the worlds.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Have you considered: if Allah should take away your hearing and your sight and set your hearts into your hearts, who is there other than Allah besides you?
Say: "Tell me, if the punishment of Allah comes to you suddenly, or openly, will it be destroyed except for the unjust people?"
And We sent not the Messengers but as bearers of glad tidings and warners; so whoever believes and reforms, there shall be no fear for them, nor shall they grieve.
As for those who reject Our revelations, they will suffer for their punishment.
Say, "I do not say to you that I possess the treasures of Allah, nor do I know the unseen." Nor do I say to you, "I am an angel." Say, "I do not follow except what is revealed to me." Say, "The blind are equal to the blind, and you do not understand."
And warn them (O Muhammad sal-Allaahu 'alayhe wa sallam) that they may come to their Lord (i.e., the Day of Resurrection), that they may have no protector besides Allah, and (that) they will have no protector besides Allah, and that they may guard (against evil).
And turn not away from those who call upon their Lord morning and evening; they will not be able to turn away from their hands, nor are they responsible for them for account of their deeds; and if you turn away from them, then you will turn away from them, and you will be among the unjust.
And We have made some of them some of them so that they may say: "Are these the ones whom Allah has bestowed upon us?" And Allah does not know those who do not know.
And when those who believe in Our Signs come to you, say: Peace be upon you, your Lord has prescribed mercy upon Himself; so if any of you does evil in ignorance, then then he will surely be kind to you, and thereafter, then He is Forgiving, Merciful.
Thus do We explain the revelations, so that the way of the criminals will be clear.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "I have been forbidden to worship those whom you invoke besides Allah." Say: "I do not follow your vain desires; I would not follow your vain desires, and I am not of the rightly guided."
Say: "I am a clear proof from my Lord, and you deny him a liar.
Say: "If I had been in your hearts, it would have been decided between me and me; and Allah knows best the wrong-doers."
And with Him is the keys of the unseen; none knows Him except Him; and He knows what is in the land and in the sea; and there is no leaf but He knows it, and there is no grain in the darkness of the earth, nor is it a dry thing in a book that is in a clear Book.
It is He Who takes your souls by night, and He knows what you have done in the day; then He raises you up in the midst of a specified term; then to Him is your return, then He will inform you of what you did.
He is the One over whom He has power over His servants, and He sends guardians over you when death comes to you when death comes to you, and they do not take away.
Then they will be returned to their Lord. He is the only Judge, and He is the swiftest of reckoning.
Say: "Who delivers you from the land of darkness and sea, when you call upon Him in humility and in secret?" Say: "If He delivers us from this, we will surely be grateful."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Allah rescues you from it and from every distress.
Say: "He is Able to send you from above you stones from above you, or from beneath your feet, or He will divide you into sects and make you taste some violence of others. See how We explain the revelations."
And your people have denied it, and it is the truth. Say: I am not a keeper over you.
And every time for every specified time, and you will know.
And when you see those who engage in Our revelations, turn away from them, turning away from them; but when they follow any other discourse, then do not sit in the company of those who do wrong.
And those who fear Allah is not responsible for their deeds; so that they may be godfearing.
And (O Muhammad) have made your religion as a sport and play for them, and the life of this world is the life of this world, and the Qur'an is a reminder for those who have passed away. There is no protector besides Him, and there is no protector for him. There is no protector besides Him, and a painful punishment for them.
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Do we invoke besides Allah that which does not profit us nor harm him, and who has been guided after Allah has guided us?
And perform prayer and fear Him; it is to Him that you shall be gathered.
It is He who created the heavens and the earth in truth, and the day He will say, "Be!" and it is. His word is the truth, the day, the Trumpet, the Trumpet, the Trumpet, the All-Knowing.
And (remember) when Ibrahim said to his father Azar: "Do you take gods as gods?
Thus did We show Abraham the kingdom of the heavens and the earth that he might be of those who have certainty.
And when the night came upon him, he saw a star; he said: "This is my Lord." But when it set, he said: "I do not love those who do not love."
And when he saw the moon rising, he said: This is my Lord; but when it set, he said: "Unless my Lord does not guide me, I will surely be among those who are astray."
And when he saw the sun rising, he said: This is my Lord; this is greater than this; but when it set, he said: "O my people! I am innocent of what you associate with Him."
“I have turned to Him (Allah), the One who created the heavens and the earth, and I am not of those who associate partners with Him.”
And his people disputed with him, saying, "Do you argue with me about Allah that He has guided me, and that I should not fear what you associate with Him? I fear that my Lord will not wish to understand. So do you not remember?"
And how should I fear those whom you associate with Allah? Do you not fear that you have joined partners with Allah for which He has sent down to you no authority? But if you know, then the two parties will be better.
As for those who believe and do not believe, it will be safe for them, and they are rightly guided.
And this is Our argument which We gave to Abraham against his people; We raise in degrees whom We will; surely your Lord is Knowing, Knowing.
And We bestowed upon him Ishaq and Ya'qub, and We guided each of them, and We guided him, and his progeny, and Sulaiman, and Sulaiman, and Solomon and Aaron and Aaron and Aaron; thus do We reward those who do good.
And Zachariah and John and Jesus and Elias; each one of them was among the righteous.
And Isma'il, Elisha, Jonah, and Lot, and all of them We preferred above the nations.
And their fathers and their spouses and their brothers, and We chose them and guided them to a straight path.
Such is the guidance of Allah, He guides whom He wills of His servants.
These are the ones whom We gave to the Book and the Prophethood and the Prophethood; but if they do not believe in it, We have made it a people who reject not.
These are the ones whom Allah has guided, so follow their guidance. Say: "I do not ask for you any reward for it. This is a reminder for the entire world."
And they did not have accepted Allah's covenant with Him that they said, "Why did He not have sent down a miracle from Allah which He has sent down?" Say: "This is the Book which Moses has sent down, and the guidance of the people which you have been given, and the guidance which you have been given, and that which you did not know."
And this is the Book which We have sent down before it, confirming what was before it, and that you may warn the Mother of Cities and those around it, and those who believe in the Hereafter believe in it, and they are called to prayer.
And who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah, or says, "I am sent down to Me," and it has been revealed to him that he should say: "I am sent down to Allah and I sent down to you what He has sent down," they will say, "I have sent down to you the Book and the punishment, so that you may turn away from their hands, and you will have a great punishment."
And indeed you have come to Us as We created you first, and left behind you what We have given you, and We do not see you with your intercessors, and We do not see your intercessors with you that you asserted.
It is Allah Who brings forth the date of the date and the date from the dead, and brings forth from the dead from the living from the dead. This is Allah, how are you turned away?
It is He Who makes the dawn overtake it, and He has made the night for rest and the sun and the moon; this is the Mighty, the Knowing.
And it is He Who has made the stars for you, that He may guide you in the darkness of the land and the sea; surely We detail the signs for a people who understand.
It is He who has created you from a single soul, then there is a place of refuge and a place of refuge. We have explained the signs for a people who understand.
It is He Who sends down water from the sky, then We produce for it all kinds of fruits and plants, from which We produce fruits from which We produce grains of palm trees and vineyards and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates and pomegranates; surely in this are signs for those who believe.
And they set up partners with Allah, that He created them, and He created them with knowledge, and He created them with knowledge and daughters; and He is exalted above what they do.
He is the Creator of the heavens and the earth; how can He have a son, and He has no consort, and He created all things, and He has knowledge of all things.
Such is Allah, your Lord; there is no god but He, the Creator of all things; therefore worship Him; He is the Guardian of everything.
No vision can grasp Him, but He comprehends the vision, and He is the Subtle, the Aware.
Indeed, there has come to you proofs from your Lord; so whoever sees it, it is for his own soul; and whoever does not see, it is for his own loss; and I am not a watcher over you.
Thus We explain the revelations to them, and they say, "You have studied," and that We may make it clear to the people who know.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord; there is no god except Him; and turn away from the polytheists.
And if Allah had willed, they would not have associated others with Him; and We have not made you a watcher over them, and you are not a guardian over them.
Do not abuse those whom they call upon besides Allah, lest they abuse Allah in spite of their ignorance, and We have made for them a fair thing for their own deeds; then to their Lord is their return, and He will inform them of what they used to do.
They swear by Allah by their strongest oaths that if a miracle came to them, they will surely believe in it. Say: "Signs of Allah is with Allah." But if they had believed, they will not believe in it.
And We will turn their hearts and their eyes, so they will not believe in it before the first time, and We will leave them blindly in their transgression blindly.
And had We sent down to them the angels, and the dead had spoken to them, and We had gathered all things before them, they would not believe unless Allah willed, but most of them are ignorant.
And thus We have made for every prophet an enemy from among the jinn and jinn, seeking each other in order to deceive each other in speech, and had your Lord willed, they would not have done it.
And so that the hearts of those who do not believe in the Hereafter may incline to it, and that they may be pleased with it, and that they may do what they are doing.
"Shall I seek other than Allah as a judge? It is He Who has sent down to you the Book (i.e. the Book) to whom He has sent down to the Book (the Qur'an) and the Book (the Qur'an).
And the word of thy Lord is true in truth and in justice; None can change His words; and He is the Hearing, the Knowing.
And if you obey most of those on earth, they will mislead you from Allah's way.
Surely your Lord knows best who has strayed from His Path, and He knows best those who are rightly guided.
If you believe in Allah, then you are the ones who believe in Allah.
And what is it that you do not eat of the Name of Allah which He has forbidden for you? He has made plain to you what Allah has forbidden for you, and He has forbidden many of them who have strayed from their own desires; surely your Lord knows best the transgressors.
And turn away from sin and sin; for those who do wrong shall be recompensed for what they used to earn.
